Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Add egg, beat well.
Turn mixer to low, gradually add flour mixture. Stir in morsels.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Remove and cool completely. Makes 6 dozen 2 inch cookies.

title: chocolate mint pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in saucepan over low heat.
Beat sugar in cream cheese; add remaining milk, the chocolate mixture and peppermint and beat until smooth.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped topping.
Spoon into crust and freeze.

title: shrimp scampi for two
directions: Soak fish in buttermilk overnight or for 4 to 6 hours.
Wash well, removing buttermilk.
Drain on paper towels.
Squeeze lemon juice over fish.
Roll in mixture of cracker meal, flour and small amount of cornmeal if desired.
Fry in heavy skillet (cast-iron) in enough Crisco plus 1 tablespoon butter to cover bottom of pan well.

title: salad dressing
directions: Pour boiling water over tomatoes, red peppers, green peppers and onion; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and add sugar, vinegar and canning salt.
Mix and cook 15 minutes.
Mix salad mustard with cornstarch and cook 15 minutes longer.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Remove from stove and add salad dressing.
Stir thoroughly and put in pint jars; seal.

title: sugar-free raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by level teaspoon on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix.
Roll in a ball and put on pan.
Cook at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Put a chocolate star on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Add water to juice to make 2 cups and heat to boiling point. Add Jell-O, pineapple and cranberry sauce; stir until cranberry sauce is completely melted. Stir in nuts and refrigerate until set.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box.
After set, add pineapple and bananas.
(Icing recipe follows.)

title: mexican fahitas
directions: Marinate steak in oil and vinegar overnight.
Place a little oil in pan and saute over very high heat so meat sears.
Add 2 tablespoons green peppers, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook until meat is done.

title: blender breakfast
directions: Put orange juice, sugar, dry milk, ice cubes and banana or strawberries in blender.
Blend on high speed for 1 minute or until ice is chopped and mixture is smooth.
Pour into individual glasses.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for a few minutes. Add cheese to taste. Easy! Good!
tags: Healthy Choice cream of chicken soup

title: mama's goo-ood chili
directions: Cook ground chuck until brown; drain through strainer until all fat is gone.
Finely crumble meat with hands, then put in 6-quart slow cooker.
Add all remaining ingredients, then stir to mix thoroughly.
Cook on high 2 hours, then simmer for 2 hours, then enjoy the best chili in world.

title: open house punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large serving bowl, adding the 7-Up last.
Add ice cubes or frozen ice ring.
Serve and enjoy.

title: candy pizza
directions: Heat chocolate chips and condensed milk in microwave until melted.
Pour over 1 cup Rice Krispies and stir to coat.
Press on buttered pizza pan.
Press into top the candied cherries and nuts. Drizzle melted almond bark across top or can use part of white frosting mixed with Eagle Brand.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix soup, milk, onion and parsley.
Dip chicken in soup mixture and then roll in stuffing.
Place in shallow baking dish. Pour butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Mix soup, beans, chilies, chili powder, onions and chicken in a saucepan and heat.
Mix muffin mix as directed.
Add 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and pull up onto sides. Pour heated mixture within 1/4 inch of edge.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with cheese, onions and cherry tomatoes.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix.
Store in sealed jar and mix 1 to 2 tablespoons with hot water to make 1 cup.

title: punch
directions: Mix together Kool Aid, water, sugar, frozen limeade and lemonade.
Last just before serving add 7 up, ginger ale and orange sherbet.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, pudding and eggs.
Beat well after each egg is added.
Add milk and grated chocolate and fold in chocolate chips.
Bake in tube pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in oblong pan, laying chicken on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn heat to 200° until done, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: green chili stew
directions: Ingredients may be increased or decreased according to taste. Go ahead!
Have it your way.

title: chicken in tomato cream sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Brown lightly in heated butter in large pan.
As you turn chicken to brown second side, add onion and mushrooms around edges.
Sprinkle chicken with parsley and basil.
Pour in sherry.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is cooked (about 20 minutes). Transfer chicken to warm serving dish. Stir mustard into liquid in pan.
Add tomatoes and cream. Bring to a boil, cook and stir until liquid is shiny, reduced and slightly thickened. Pour sauce over chicken and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl until smooth.
Pour batter into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream puffs(diabetic)
directions: Combine water, shortening and salt.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to low and add flour; beat until smooth and ball clings.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or golden brown and almost dry.
Makes 6 to 8.

title: hot ham buns
directions: Mix butter, mustard, poppy seed and onion and spread on the surface of buns.
Tuck a slice of ham and cheese in each bun. Arrange on a baking sheet and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes until hot.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream margarine, vanilla and peanut butter together, adding powdered sugar until desired consistency is reached.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and Crisco in top of double boiler; keep mixture in boiler over low heat and dip balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: baked corn custard
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and place in a shallow baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan combine molasses, corn syrup and vinegar. Cook, stirring occasionally till a little mixture dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat, add 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine.
Stir only long enough to mix.
Pour over popcorn.
Toss until coated.
Quickly shape into 2 1/2-inch balls.
Makes 10.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix until smooth.
Slice a thin slice off tops of tomatoes and carefully remove insides; invert on paper towel to drain.
Fill with cream cheese mixture.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix together and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cut asparagus spears in pieces about 3/4 inch long and place in bottom of a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and hard-boiled eggs.
Cover with white sauce.
Add another layer of asparagus, cheese, egg and pimento; cover with white sauce.
Top with buttered bread crumbs or crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake in a moderate oven and cook until crumbs are crisp and brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mash bananas (hands work best).
Add all other ingredients. Either grease and flour pans or spray with cooking spray.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until done (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: potato sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
In a greased 2-quart casserole dish, layer half of the potatoes, half of the soup mixture and half of the sausage.
Repeat ending with sausage.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven, uncovered, for 2 minutes.

title: four layer salad
directions: Make a bed of lettuce in the bowl.
Place a layer of English peas on the lettuce, then a layer of chopped onion.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over onions.
Top with package of shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: mock angel food cake
directions: Sift flour 5 times, then add sugar and salt.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until about half stiff, then add baking powder.
Beat until it stands in peaks.
Now pour boiling water over flour and sugar and stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla. Fold in egg whites until well blended.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan in slow oven at 320°.

title: minted cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumber, onion, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper. Toss well.
Add yogurt and fresh mint.
Stir well to combine. Refrigerate.

title: peach pear jam
directions: Wash, peel, pit and grind or finely chop peaches, pears and cherries.
Prepare jam according to directions on package of MCP Pectin for Peach Pear Jam.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter and add sugar, cocoa and milk. Bring to boil over medium heat. Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Return to boil. Remove from heat, add oatmeal uncooked. Stir until mixed well.
Spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Top with herb stuffing Pepperidge Farm. Add grated cheese on top.

title: steamed spinach
directions: Squeeze and dry spinach thoroughly.
Melt butter and chop onion fine.
Mix egg yolks with spinach and add all ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into spinach.

title: foiled hobo stew(method:  foil)
directions: Put meat for one serving on a large foil square.
Add remaining ingredients.
Seal foil with a double foil.
Cook on hot coals for 45 to 60 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add extracts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° (do not preheat oven) for 1 1/2 hours +.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Remove cream cheese from fridge.
Put evaporated milk in freezer.
Add 1 cup hot water to Jell-O.
Place in fridge until syrupy.
Whip.
Add sugar and vanilla to cheese and beat.
Whip evaporated milk until it peaks.
Mix with cheese mixture.
Add crushed pineapple, if desired.
Press 1/2 of cracker mixture into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Sprinkle balance of crackers over top.

title: hush puppies
directions: In
large
bowl
mix
together	meal, flour, buttermilk, eggs, onion, sugar, garlic and paprika.	Bring 4 cups oil to a boil
in large
pot.
Drop	by
teaspoonfuls
in hot oil until brown. Yield: 50 hush puppies.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain. Spoon beef into an 8-inch baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs; beat until smooth. Pour mixture over casserole, covering evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: melted cheese spread
directions: Cut up cheese.
Add milk; put on medium heat until cheese is melted.
Add egg and cornstarch; cook until thick.
Cool.
Makes a good sandwich on rye with slice of shave ham.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Add coconut, chocolate chips and nuts in layers.
Pour milk over nuts.
Do not stir.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: rice and beef supper
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart greased, covered oven dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch pan, mix the first 5 ingredients.
In bowl combine the next 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle on top of rhubarb.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: easy vegetable linguine
directions: Cook linguine as directed.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onion and broccoli in fat. Crumble bacon.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Serve with additional cheese.
Can be served warm or cold.
Makes 2 servings.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse the dry green split peas.
Pick out any stems or stones. Put peas, ham hock, onion, pepper and water in a pot.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until ham hock is tender.
Remove ham hock and cut meat from bone.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Return meat into soup.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: quiche parmesana
directions: Place all ingredients (minus pie shell) in blender.
Cover; blend at high speed at least 1 minute.
Pour mixture into crust. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy vegetable-beef soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dream cake
directions: Bake cake mix as per recipe on box.
While still hot, poke small holes with toothpick.
Heat Jell-O up and pour over cake slowly to drain in cake.
Chill completely in refrigerator until cold.
Frost with whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: rice and gravy
directions: Cook the rice, then meat and seasoning, then put gravy.
Put the rice and gravy in the to 72 minits and it is radey.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours at 350° in tube pan (Bundt pan is nice to cook this in).

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Melt chocolate and shortening in large saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread into pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies pull away from pan.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
If desired, before cutting, spread with chocolate frosting.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Mix basil, garlic and oil.
Add tofu; blend.
Mix in pine nuts.
Pour into crust and top with artichoke hearts and bread crumbs.
Drizzle oil on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar and flour. Add the corn syrup, coconut, pineapple, eggs and vanilla; mix well.

Pour into pastry shell. Drizzle with butter. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Cover loosely with foil if the top browns too quickly. Cool on a wire rack. Chill before cutting.
Store in the refrigerator. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg-cheese dish(breakfast - brunch)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan generously.
Spread the bread cubes over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cheese cubes over bread.
In bowl beat eggs.
Add milk and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour over cheese-bread in pan carefully.
Cover with plastic or foil and place in fridge overnight.
Next morning sprinkle bacon bits over mixture and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In blender, grind cookies up fine.
Add melted butter and mix.
Press into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Melt chocolate in microwave, stirring every 30 seconds.
Pour half into pan over crust.
Smooth and spread over entire crust.
Keep remaining chocolate warm. Blend peanut butter and butter together.
Slowly beat in confectioners sugar; add vanilla.
Beat.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Pour remaining chocolate over peanut butter layer.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut into bars and serve.
Very rich!

title: granny's rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Slowly add 9 to 10 cups flour until sticky dough forms.
Turn out onto greased bowl and turn to cover top with grease.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and form rolls.
Place in greased pan and let rise until double.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Brush margarine over tops of hot rolls.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: hot chili sauce
directions: Wash tomatoes and dip into boiling water long enough to loosen skins,
then remove skins and core. Cut up and place in colander to
drain.
Save
drained
juice
and
put in 8 quart kettle
and boil
about 30 minutes. Add other ingredients and cook
moderately fast, stirring often until sauce thickens to desired consistency (about 2 1/2 hours). Store in pint or 1/2 pint jars.
This
sauce may also be served as a cocktail sauce on shrimp or oysters.

title: jalapeno roll-ups
directions: Combine all filling ingredients in mixing bowl. Mix well. On each tortilla, spread about 1/2 cup mixture. Roll up tightly (jelly roll fashion). Wrap in Saran Wrap. Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Cut each tortilla into 12 slices. Makes 48.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix well together and put into a greased loaf pan; bake at 300° until brown.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Thaw spinach. Mix with ingredients; pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: gingerbread cookies(50 to 60 cookies)
directions: Combine the sugar, ginger, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add the melted margarine, evaporated milk and molasses.
Add the extracts, if desired.
Mix well.
Add the flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring constantly.
The dough should be stiff enough to handle without sticking to fingers.
Knead the dough for a smoother texture.
Add up to 1/2 cup additional flour, if necessary, to prevent sticking.

title: crunchy jungle cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars thoroughly.
Add the eggs and vanilla; blend.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture. Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: low-fat green chili casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open cans of green chilies and rinse in colander with water; set aside.
Take egg whites and evaporated milk; whisk until just frothy.
Spray ungreased 8 x 9-inch pan with Pam or other low saturated fat oil.
Put a layer of chilies, then sprinkle mixture of 2 cheeses (I use quite a bit).
Then pour 1/3 of milk and egg white mixture.
This mixture does not need to cover the layer.
Repeat this layering (chilies, cheese and milk mixture) until you are at the top.
Pour tomato sauce on top to cover.
Bake until bubbly throughout, anywhere from 20 to 30 minutes.
Take out.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: indian salmon croquettes
directions: In large bowl, drain and pulverize salmon.
Add all ingredients; mixing thoroughly.
Mixture should be moist and not too chunky.
Pour top olive oil into heavy iron skillet and heat over medium heat.
Shape croquettes to desired size, dust with flour on both sides and cook, turning them once until golden brown on both sides, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: microwave chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 2-quart glass casserole dish with salt and pepper.
Cover with water and microwave, covered, on High for 40 minutes.
Saute onion, peppers, mushrooms and garlic until onion is translucent.
Drain chicken, reserving liquid.

title: greek salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar and seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes, cucumbers, onions and pour dressing over all. Garnish with black olives and Feta cheese.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cover bottom of pot with oil and brown 3 to 4 minced garlic cloves.
Add tomato sauce and the remaining spices according to taste.
Brown the meat and drain fat.
Add the meat and let simmer 1 hour.
Serves 3 to 4.
Cook until desired thickness, the longer you cook it, the thicker it gets.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Add blueberry pie filling and crushed pineapple. Place in refrigerator until firm.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Spread on top of congealed salad.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute chopped onions and peppers until tender in shortening. Add ground meat and brown.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasoning.
Put in covered dish and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Serve.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Put soup, cheese, onion and sour cream in large mixing bowl; stir together.
Add potatoes and salt and pepper to taste and mix again.
Pour into 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a roasting pan.
Bake at a low heat (200° to 300°) for several hours, until done.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Mix margarine and brown sugar in cast iron deep fry pan on the stove.
Spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Remove from stove and place pineapple rings on top of mixture, placing a cherry in the center of each pineapple ring.
In a large bowl, place cake mix, eggs and pineapple juice.
Mix well, mixture will thick, heavy and fluffy.
Spread on top of pineapple in cast iron pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake is golden brown and a toothpick stuck in the center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan for 5 minutes then turn over onto cake plate.
Best served warm.

title: striped pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed, baking in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes at once down through the cake to the pan with round handle of wooden spoon.
Holes should be about 1-inch apart.

title: bob hope's favorite chicken hash
directions: Cut chicken in fine strips, crumble bacon and combine with the onion, butter, lemon juice and seasonings.
Saute until thoroughly heated in the butter, and shortly before serving add the sherry and sour cream.
Do not allow to cook after adding the last two ingredients.
Just heat through.

title: lasagna
directions: Grate large chunk of Mozzarella and Romano cheese; set aside. Brown in skillet celery, onion and ground beef.
Mix in saucepan tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, vinegar, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add meat mixture to sauce and simmer 3 hours.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Spread 1/3 sauce in large baking dish.
Put layer of noodles over sauce.
Sprinkle cheese over noodles. Repeat and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Beat shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture, oats and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Spread in ungreased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lula's fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and bake
in
greased	tube
pan for 4 hours at 250°.
Put a pan of
water over cake and one of water under cake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill 24 hours for thick or 3 hours for creamy smooth.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Wash broccoli and remove any leaves on coarse stems.
Put broccoli in kettle and add half the stock or broth.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 7 minutes or until tender.
Remove broccoli from stock with slotted spoon and chop coarsely.
Add remaining stock, milk, ham, salt and pepper to the stock in kettle and stir well.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cream, cheese, butter and broccoli and heat until cheese is melted.
Do not boil.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix flour, butter, and powdered sugar.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased square pan (8x8x2). Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients about 3 minutes on medium speed or until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust. Bake about 25 minutes longer or just until no imprint remains when touched lightly in the center.
Cool.
Cut into 2 inch squares.

title: hickory smoked chicken
directions: Place chicken on baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle with seasoning.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.
While chicken is baking, melt butter in saucepan with garlic over low heat.
Cook for a minute.
Add tomato sauce and hickory seasoning. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove chicken from oven; brush generously with sauce.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine onions, green chiles, soup, sour cream, olives and 1/4 of each cheese. Set aside 1 1/2 cups of the combine mixture. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Lay each tortilla flat and put in mixture.
Roll up and put rolls in pan. Cover tortillas with the remaining mixture. Sprinkle remaining cheese over the tortillas. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in oven, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Enjoy.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly with fork; stir in milk, pumpkin and margarine.
Blend dry ingredients and stir in until flour mixture is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fold in raisins.
Fill greased muffin cups or paper baking cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon sugar over each muffin.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: better than sin cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.

When cake is done, poke holes in first layer and spread 1/2 of the condensed milk on top and then 1/2 of the caramel, heat the hot fudge and put 1/2 of it on the first layer, repeat process on second layer.
Add cool whip on top and cherries to garnish.

title: monteray carrot cake
directions: Measure into sifter the flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and sugar.
Sift into mixing bowl and add salad oil, eggs (one at a time) and vanilla.
Beat until light. Stir in carrots.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish with a nonfat cooking spray.
With a stiff brush, scrub zucchini well.
Cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
In a medium bowl, combine flour and 1/2 teaspoon lite salt, 1/2 teaspoon oregano and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Toss zucchini slices in seasoned flour to coat them well.
Slowly heat liquid Butter Buds in a nonstick skillet.
Saute zucchini slices until golden brown, about 4 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Cover bottom of baking dish with zucchini.
Top with tomato slices.

title: my mom's strawberry bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients.
In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Set aside.
Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake one hour or more at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Contains 195 calories per 1/2-inch slice.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and reserve 2/3 cup for topping (add nuts; optional).
Add oil, water and eggs to remaining batter and beat.
Sprinkle topping over batter and top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: no egg ice cream
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar to fresh peaches.
Blend.
Add 2 cups sugar, Pet milk and apricot nectar to peaches.
Mix and pour in freezer. Fill 1 gallon ice cream freezer with milk and freeze.

title: hamburger 'n hot dogs
directions: In a pot, cook hamburger with garlic; drain oil.
Add soup mix, onions and celery to hamburger mixture.
Simmer on low heat. Chop hot dogs into bite size.
Add hot dogs and Ragu sauce to hamburger mixture; set on low heat to simmer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits; fill with apples.
Pinch together.
Bring to a boil the butter, sugar, cinnamon and 7-Up.
Pour over Apple Dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick taco salad
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
In same skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni as package directs.
Stir in meat mixture, salsa and chili powder; continue cooking over low heat 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through.
Arrange lettuce on serving platter or bowl.
Top with beef/rice mixture, tomato and cheese.
Garnish or serve with tortilla chips.

title: piroshki
directions: Remove pastry shells from package and let stand at room temperature to thaw 30 minutes.

title: coke roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with seasoned salt and sear in oil on all sides.
Remove and blot off fat from roast.
Place roast in a foil lined pan.
Pour Coke and chili sauce over roast, then Worcestershire sauce.
Cover loosely with foil and bake 3 hours at 325°.
It will have a barbecued flavor and tastes good the next day, too.

title: cheater's cheese souffle
directions: Sprinkle the sliced chicken with 2 tablespoons flour (or put both into a bag and shake).
Heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat.
Add the chicken and flour and saute until lightly browned (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Remove chicken from pan and keep warm. Combine garlic, ginger, vinegar, chicken stock, honey and soy sauce.
Add to the same pan and bring to a boil; stir until thickened, fragrant and reduced by about half (about 5 minutes). Add chicken to the pan, stirring well.
Sprinkle with scallions and heat through.
Serve over steamed rice.
Serves 4.

title: rye log
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well, add corned beef.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator, covered.

title: dorothy's new england apple-raisin bread
directions: Blend flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, salt and spices in a large bowl.
Stir together buttermilk, applesauce and butter.
Combine above, stirring until just moistened.
Fold in raisins and nuts and turn into greased and floured 6 1/2 C ring mold.

title: lazy man's chile
directions: Brown the meat with the diced onion and seasonings.
Add tomato soup (do not dilute).
Add kidney beans (do not dilute). Let simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Fold sweetened condensed milk and lemonade concentrate into whipped topping; spoon into crusts.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish, if desired.

title: smooth chocolate dip
directions: Whisk ingredients in a small bowl.
Makes about 3/4 cup of dip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mixing well.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cover with 1 can (4 or 5 oz.) green chilies, drained and 6 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spread remaining batter over top. Bake in hot oven, 400° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut them into small cubes with some large cubes.
Put them and the soup, water and milk in a pan.
Bring to a boil until potatoes are done.
Season with celery seed and garlic while cooking.

title: old-fashion herb stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread cubes on baking sheet; bake 10 minutes or until dry.
Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onions, celery and carrot; cover and cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add broth, thyme, sage, paprika and pepper; bring to a simmer.
Stir in bread pieces; mix well.
Remove pan from heat; set aside.
Coat a 1-1/2 quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Spoon stuffing into dish.
Cover and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Blend in milk, oleo, pineapple and bread crumbs.
Pour into a well-greased casserole and bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes at 350°.
Especially good served with baked ham instead of sweet potatoes.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar (exact amount depends upon sweetness desired) and salt and stir until well mixed. Add scalded milk gradually, while stirring constantly. Add vanilla. Add nutmeg or cinnamon, if desired. Bake in 6 or 8 custard cups or 1 1/2-quart casserole. Place cups in a shallow pan containing warm water and bake in a moderate 325° oven 45 minutes for the cups and 50 to 60 minutes for casserole. Test by inserting a silver knife into center of the custard.
If knife comes out clean, the custard is done.

title: swiss cheese bread
directions: Trim crust from bread leaving bottom crust intact.
Make diagonal cuts 1-inch apart in bread.
Do not cut completely through bread into slices, but leave bottom crust intact.

title: vegetable potato soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in covered saucepan until tender. Mash until fluffy.
Add milk; mix well.
Cook remaining vegetables and salt in beef broth in covered saucepan until tender, about 15 minutes.
Blend with potato mixture.
Stir in black pepper and butter.
Serve hot.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nutmeg, salt, milk and flavoring.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until pies are done.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook and cool Rice-A-Roni according to package directions. Drain liquid from marinated artichoke hearts and mix with mayonnaise.
Add all ingredients and marinade to Rice-A-Roni. Garnish with artichoke hearts.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and cool.
Mix all ingredients and chill in bowl.
(A jello salad bowl is best.)
Unmold salad and serve with crackers.

title: brisket marinate
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and put on brisket.
Wrap with foil and put in refrigerator overnight.
Mix Worcestershire sauce and season salt together.
Pour over brisket.
Rewrap and bake at 300° for 5 to 7 hours, or until tender.

title: old fashioned ground beef soup
directions: Brown the ground chuck with onions, celery and bell pepper. Add remaining ingredients and cover with water until all vegetables are covered.
Add stew mix and cook until vegetables are tender.
Makes a large pot of soup that may be frozen indefinitely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In casserole dish, add layers of broccoli, onions, eggs and celery soup.
Make a cream sauce of melted butter, flour and salt. Stir well.
Add milk and cheese; blend until melted.
Pour over other ingredients.
Sprinkle with grated cheese or Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion lightly in butter.
Add chili sauce, water and sugar; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add mustard, lemon juice, vinegar, Worcestershire, salt and garlic.
Simmer until mixture is thick.

title: rechele's red beans and rice
directions: In a large pan cook onions, green peppers and garlic in butter for about 3 minutes. Add beans, sausage, tomato sauce and worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce. Tabasco sauce and red pepper. Reduce heat to a simmer, cover and cook for 15 minutes. Boil rice. Serve mixture over rice.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar, peanut butter, and vanilla together. Roll into 1/2 inch balls; chill. Melt chocolate chips and dip peanut butter balls. Place on wax paper.

title: blueberry-oat muffins
directions: Combine oats and sour milk in small bowl.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and brown sugar; stir well to blend.
Add egg and melted margarine to oat mixture; stir well. Add oat mixture all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just until all ingredients are moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Fill well-greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: date skillet cookies
directions: Cook first four ingredients for 15 minutes (medium heat) in an electric skillet.
When cooked, stir in nuts, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Roll in hand to make small balls and then roll in coconut.
Put on waxed paper on cookie sheet.

title: swiss steak
directions: Fry steak in oil until brown.
Place in roasting pan or crock-pot.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Simmer at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: mango chutney
directions: Peel and slice mangos.
Salt and cover with water overnight. Strain and wash.
Boil all ingredients (except sugar) until tender.
Add sugar and simmer another 2 hours.
Bottle and seal.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Add salt to water in large cooking pan.
Bring water to a boil. Add macaroni.
When water returns to boil, cook macaroni for 7 to 9 minutes.
DO NOT OVERCOOK.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking. Drain in colander.
Run hot water through macaroni to rinse well. Combine eggs, melted butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix in cooked macaroni.
Arrange macaroni mixture and grated cheese alternately in buttered casserole with top layer being cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until surface is golden brown and cheese is crusted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: "sinful pie"
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine in pie plate.
Press evenly in bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add milk and pudding mix.
Beat until thickened. Spread over banana slices; put pineapple over this.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: fried squash
directions: Slice the squash into thin rounds. Dip in beaten egg then coat with the cornmeal. Fry in oil on medium heat on both sides. Drain on paper towel and salt lightly before serving.

title: momma's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with several pats of butter and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will need 1 new 8 x 10-inch flowerpot, silk flowers and candy gummy worms.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and make into soft balls. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients except peas, beans and pasta in large pot. Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add peas, beans and pasta and cook an additional 1/2 hour or until all vegetables are tender.
Add extra water during cooking if soup starts to get too thick.

title: pepper relish(makes about 6 to 8 pints)
directions: Grind and soak peppers and onions in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Drain and add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 30 to 35 minutes.
Seal at once.
Delicious on sandwiches!

title: goochies
directions: Line cookie sheet with tinfoil. Break crackers and place on foil.
Sprinkle nuts over crackers.
Boil margarine, butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
Spoon over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: golden beef quiche
directions: Lightly brown beef and onions.
Drain off any grease.
Put meat in crust.
Mix undiluted soup and rest of ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in 375° oven until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter together until smooth.
Add corn flakes and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let harden.

title: pixie salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients until well blended.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Cook rice according to pkg. directions.

title: pecan praline ice cream
directions: Place pecans in butter in a skillet and toast.
In a separate bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Mix in pecans.
Pour mix into freezer, add milk to fill line.
Follow ice cream manufacturers directions.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, milk, onions, egg, salt and pepper; mix well. Pour into pan, top with pimientos and green peppers.
Stir just enough to mix.
Dot top with butter and bake at 350° until done.

title: cheesy lasagne
directions: Melt margarine and stir in flour and salt.

Cook, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in milk. Boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Add Swiss cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Cook and stir over low heat until cheeses are melted and mix remaining ingredients along with Parmesan cheese. Spread 1/4 of the cheese sauce mixture in ungreased dish. Top with 4 uncooked noodles.
Spread 1 cup cottage cheese mixture over noodles. Repeat with 4 noodles, the remaining noodles and remaining cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
